<paragraph id="8BF136C4893FFF9BFF578BD3C637FCF9" blockId="57.[151,1436,303,852]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
Comment: 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF4B35893FFF9BFEDC8BD3C078FE6F" author="Rode, P." box="[333,544,424,450]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="227 - 252" refId="ref47439" refString="Rode, P. (1941) Catalogue des types de mammiferes du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Ordre des chiropteres. Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris, 13, 227 - 252." type="journal article" year="1941">Rode (1941: 247)</bibRefCitation>
listed a 
<typeStatus id="54F58866893FFF9BFD1B8BD3C0A9FE6F" box="[650,753,424,450]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">holotype</typeStatus>
for 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47893FFF9BFCB78BD3C1A5FE6C" authority="Hilarii" authorityName="Hilarii I. Geoffroy" authorityYear="1824" box="[806,1021,424,449]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6893FFF9BFCB78BD3C1A5FE6C" box="[806,1021,424,449]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Vespertilio Hilarii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion id="498AF826893FFF9BFB9E8BD3C632FE6F" box="[1039,1130,424,450]" country="Ireland" name="Monaghan" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">MNHN</collectingRegion>
834) and 
<specimenCount id="9D48FD4D893FFF9BFB798BD3C7C4FE6F" box="[1256,1436,424,450]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">three paratypes</specimenCount>
(
<collectingRegion id="498AF826893FFF9BFF0F8BABC2A2FE47" box="[158,250,464,490]" country="Ireland" name="Monaghan" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">MNHN</collectingRegion>
835, 836, 838), although these latter were not found by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF4B35893FFF9BFC348BABC6B1FE47" author="Carter, D. C. &amp; Dolan, P. G." box="[933,1257,464,490]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 136" refId="ref44526" refString="Carter, D. C. &amp; Dolan, P. G. (1978) Catalogue of type specimens of Neotropical bats in selected European museums. Special Publication The Museum Texas Tech University, 15, 1 - 136, Lubbock, Texas." type="journal article" year="1978">Carter &amp; Dolan (1978: 80)</bibRefCitation>
. It would have been unusual if Geoffroy to have designated a 
<typeStatus id="54F58866893FFF9BFD288B83C147FDBF" box="[697,799,504,530]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">holotype</typeStatus>
in 1824, and since Rode did not expressly designate a 
<typeStatus id="54F58866893FFF9BFF06885BC35DFD97" box="[151,261,544,570]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">lectotype</typeStatus>
, all individuals of the type series are to be considered as 
<typeStatus id="54F58866893FFF9BFC39885BC64AFD97" box="[936,1042,544,570]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">syntypes</typeStatus>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF4B35893FFF9BFB8F885BC6ACFD97" author="Davis, W. B." box="[1054,1268,544,570]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="245 - 274" refId="ref44768" refString="Davis, W. B. (1966) Review of South American bats of the genus Eptesicus. The Southwestern Naturalist, 11 (2), 245 - 274." type="journal article" year="1966">Davis (1966: 257)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that &quot;Until direct comparisons of [
<collectingRegion id="498AF826893FFF9BFE608833C008FDCF" box="[497,592,584,610]" country="Ireland" name="Monaghan" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">MNHN</collectingRegion>
] No. 834 can be made with 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47893FFF9BFC068833C658FDCC" baseAuthorityName="Palisot de Beauvois" baseAuthorityYear="1796" box="[919,1024,584,609]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6893FFF9BFC068833C658FDCC" box="[919,1024,584,609]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">E. fuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6893FFF9BFBA88833C6B0FDCC" box="[1081,1256,584,609]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47893FFF9BFBA88833C6BBFDCC" baseAuthorityName="Desmarest" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[1081,1251,584,609]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">E. brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
it seems advisable to retain 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47893FFF9BFEA9880BC020FD27" authority="Geoffroy" authorityName="Geoffroy" authorityYear="1824" box="[312,632,624,650]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hilarii">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6893FFF9BFEA9880BC05DFD24" box="[312,517,624,649]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Vespertilio hilarii</emphasis>
Geoffroy
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47893FFF9BFCD6880BC6D1FD27" authority="(Desmarest)" baseAuthorityName="Desmarest" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[839,1161,624,650]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6893FFF9BFCD6880BC1B7FD24" box="[839,1007,624,649]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">E. brasiliensis</emphasis>
(Desmarest)
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<specimenCount id="9D48FD4D893FFF9BFB5B880BC724FD27" box="[1226,1404,624,650]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">three paratypes</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47893FFF9BFF0688E3C2B8FD1C" authorityName="Geoffroy" authorityYear="1824" box="[151,224,664,689]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hilarii">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6893FFF9BFF0688E3C2B8FD1C" box="[151,224,664,689]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">hilarii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are much smaller than the 
<typeStatus id="54F58866893FFF9BFDB588E3C0D2FD1F" box="[548,650,664,690]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">holotype</typeStatus>
and appear to represent the species 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47893FFF9BFBA988E3C766FD1F" authority="(Dobson)" baseAuthorityName="Dobson" box="[1080,1342,664,690]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dorianus">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6893FFF9BFBA988E3C699FD1C" box="[1080,1217,664,689]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">E. dorianus</emphasis>
(Dobson)
</taxonomicName>
&quot;, which according to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDF4B35893FFF9BFEA088BBC069FD77" author="Simmons, N. B." box="[305,561,704,730]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="312 - 529" refId="ref47522" refString="Simmons, N. B. (2005) Order Chiroptera. In: Wilson, D. E. &amp; Reeder, D. M. (Eds). Mammal species of the world: a taxonomic and geographic reference. Third edition, Vol. 1. Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore, pp. 312 - 529." type="book chapter" year="2005">Simmons (2005: 454)</bibRefCitation>
is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47893FFF9BFD6C88BBC1D9FD74" baseAuthorityName="d'Orbigny" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[765,897,704,729]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="furinalis">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6893FFF9BFD6C88BBC1D9FD74" box="[765,897,704,729]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">E. furinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. On the basis of measurements of ZMB 3912 (forearm = 39.0mm; metacarp of 3 
<superScript id="7C3B9B8C893FFF9BFDD58893C009FD5B" attach="left" box="[580,593,744,758]" fontSize="6" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">rd</superScript>
finger = 37.1mm; upper tooth row = 5.95mm; breadth across upper molars = 7.2mm; mandible = 11.8mm), we conclude that ZMB 3912 belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47893FFF9BFBC78968C76AFC81" baseAuthorityName="d'Orbigny" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[1110,1330,787,812]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="furinalis">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6893FFF9BFBC78968C76AFC81" box="[1110,1330,787,812]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Eptesicus furinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<collectingRegion id="498AF826893FFF9BFAD38969C7C3FC81" box="[1346,1435,786,812]" country="Ireland" name="Monaghan" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">MNHN</collectingRegion>
No. 834 seems to be the only representative of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47893FFF9BFD2F8940C13EFCF9" baseAuthorityName="Desmarest" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[702,870,827,852]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6893FFF9BFD2F8940C13EFCF9" box="[702,870,827,852]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">E. brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the type series.
</paragraph>
